item.description:
Exclusions Pregnant women beware:
&ldquo;Muslim children exposed to Ramadan fasting in utero during first trimester had significantly lower scores in maths, reading, and writing tests (taken at the age of 7 years) than Muslim children who were not exposed to Ramadan fasting in utero.&rdquo; /&hellip;
Another extensive census-based study of Muslim populations in Uganda (n = 80,000) and Iraq (n = 250,000) demonstrated that exposure to Ramadan fasting during the first month of pregnancy increased the risk of mental or learning disability in offspring by 50% and psychological disability by 63%!
